1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE BILL 3757 By: Sterling
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Turnpike Authority;
amending 69 O.S. 2021, Section 1705, as amended by
8 Section 572, Chapter 486, O.S.L. 2025 (69 O.S. Supp.
2025, Section 1705), which relates to Oklahoma
9 Turnpike Authority powers and duties; stating
applicability; making determination of certain date
10 of legislative authorization; making certain
requirements of Oklahoma Turnpike Authority for
11 turnpike projects; requiring certain projects lapse
if deadline is not met; stating no impairment to
12 certain contracts or revenues; requiring certain
report be filed; defining term; and providing an
13 effective date.
14
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 69 O.S. 2021, Section 1705, as
19 amended by Section 572, Chapter 486, O.S.L. 2025 (69 O.S. Supp.
20 2025, Section 1705), is amended to read as follows:
21 Section 1705. The Oklahoma Turnpike Authority is hereby
22 authorized and empowered:
23 (a) To adopt bylaws for the regulation of its affairs and
24 conduct of its business.
Req. No. 15327 Page 1

1 (b) To adopt an official seal and alter the same at pleasure.
2 (c) To maintain an office at such place or places within the
3 state as it may designate.
4 (d) To sue and be sued in contract, reverse condemnation,
5 equity, mandamus and similar actions in its own name, plead and be
6 impleaded; provided, that any and all actions at law or in equity
7 against the Authority shall be brought in the county in which the
8 principal office of the Authority shall be located, or in the county
9 of the residence of the plaintiff, or the county where the cause of
10 action arose. All privileges granted to the Authority and duties
11 enjoined upon the Authority by the provisions of Sections 1701
12 through 1734 of this title may be enforced in a court of competent
13 jurisdiction in an action in mandamus.
14 (e) To construct, maintain, repair and operate turnpike
15 projects and highways, with their access and connecting roads, at
16 such locations and on such routes as it shall determine to be
17 feasible and economically sound; provided, that until specifically
18 authorized by the Legislature, the Authority shall be authorized to
19 construct and operate toll turnpikes only at the following
20 locations:
21 (1) The Turner Turnpike between Oklahoma City and Tulsa.
22 (2) The Southwestern (H.E. Bailey) Turnpike between Oklahoma
23 City and Wichita Falls, Texas.
24
